PIM is dependent on MySQL. 

Instruction on howto install, configure and create the database with the proper
permissions you can find in the MySQL manual.

To import the database structure you can use the command:

$ mysql -u pim -p pim < db-structure.sql

To configure the database connection for PIM change the variables appropriatly
and add its contents to pim.conf in the root of the PIM project.

[database]
host = "localhost"
username = "pim"
password = "pim"
database = "pim"

Here are some useful commands for testing purposes. When the Administration
interface is finished these should be removed.
drop table user;
drop table location;
drop table datahamster_extra;
drop table datahamster;
drop table category;
drop table address;

insert into address values (NULL, 'teststraat', 1, NULL, '1337AA', 'Hamsterstad');
insert into category values (NULL, 'sector1', 'test sector 1');
insert into category values (NULL, 'sector2', 'test sector 2');
insert into category values (NULL, 'sector3', 'test sector 3');
insert into datahamster values (NULL, 1, 1, NULL, 'test hamster 1', 'test dep 1', 'test web 1', 'test email 1');
insert into datahamster values (NULL, 1, 2, NULL, 'test hamster 2', 'test dep 2', 'test web 2', 'test email 2');
insert into datahamster values (NULL, 1, 3, NULL, 'test hamster 3', 'test dep 3', 'test web 3', 'test email 3');
insert into location values (NULL, 1, 'Test');
insert into datahamster_extra values (NULL, 1, 'test', 'test');
insert into datahamster_extra values (NULL, 2, 'test', 'test');
insert into datahamster_extra values (NULL, 3, 'test', 'test');
-- insert into user values (mysql_insert_id);
